		<div id="comment_body_65021611"><p><div class="quote"><p>not a subjective measure</p></div><p>True, but it has become more complicated.
Fake news is the <b>intentional</b> dissemination of false information to influence people's opinions and actions.
<br> <br>
For example, fake news about signs of life on the moon published in the 19th century is a classic example, where the publisher later admitted it was a lie.
It did, however, attract more subscriptions.
And Russia has spread disinformation about a plane crash in Ukraine in 2014, and has several "troll factories" etc...
<br> <br>
But Trump has often used the term as a<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
